#: ../../C/cybercrud.rst:10
msgid ""
"[coined by Ted Nelson] Obfuscatory tech-talk. Verbiage with a high "
":ref:`MEGO` factor. The computer equivalent of bureaucratese."
msgstr "[Ted Nelsonが造った] 不明瞭にする技術用語。高い\\ :ref:`MEGO`\\ 度の言葉遣い。お役所言葉のコンピューター版。"

#: ../../C/cybercrud.rst:15
msgid ""
"Incomprehensible stuff embedded in email. First there were the \"Received\" "
"headers that show how mail flows through systems, then MIME (Multi-purpose "
"Internet Mail Extensions) headers and part boundaries, and now huge blocks "
"of radix-64 for PEM (Privacy Enhanced Mail) or PGP (Pretty Good Privacy) "
"digital signatures and certificates of authenticity. This stuff all serves a"
" purpose and good user interfaces should hide it, but all too often users "
"are forced to wade through it."
msgstr ""
"eメールに埋め込まれた理解不能なもの。最初はメールがシステムをどう流れるかを示す「Received」ヘッダがあり、次にMIME(Multi-"
"purpose Internet Mail Extensions)ヘッダとパート境界、そして今やPEM(Privacy Enhanced "
"Mail)やPGP(Pretty Good "
"Privacy)のデジタル署名と真正性証明書のための巨大なradix-64のブロックがあります。これらはすべて目的を果たすものであり、優れたユーザーインターフェースはそれを隠すべきですが、あまりに頻繁にユーザーはそれをかき分けて進むことを強いられます。"
